tarted%20to%20sell%20itself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bclimate%20haven%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20cheap%20housing%20and%20a%20more%20stable%20climate.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Buffalo.%20The%20city's%20population%20has%20since%201970%20been%20on%20a%20long%2C%20steady%20decline%20as%20its%20thriving%20industrial%20sector%20was%20hollowed%20out.%20Now%2C%20the%20city's%20leaders%20have%20sensed%20an%20opportunity%20to%20revitalize%20the%20region.%20Buffalo's%20natural%20characteristics%20provide%20a%20good%20starting%20point%20%E2%80%94%20its%20high%20temperature%20in%20July%20of%2079%20degrees%20is%20much%20cooler%20than%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20for%20instance.%20And%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Emergency%20Management%20Agency%2C%20the%20city%20has%20been%20hit%20by%20only%2027%20federally%20declared%20disasters%20since%201953.%20Compare%20that%20with%20the%2080%20disasters%20that%20have%20hit%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20and%20the%2041%20disasters%20in%20Miami-Dade%20County.%20Then%20there's%20its%20abundant%20freshwater%20from%20Lake%20Erie%2C%20relatively%20cheap%20housing%20market%20%E2%80%94%20Zillow%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fhome-values%2F17222%2Fbuffalo-ny%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshows%20that%20the%20median%20home%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20city%20was%20%24215%2C000%20as%20of%20October%20%E2%80%94%20and%20robust%20infrastructure%20from%20the%20city's%20previous%20life%20as%20a%20manufacturing%20center.%20With%20all%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20Buffalo%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20stage%20a%20serious%20comeback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffalo's%20leaders%20have%20decided%20to%20capitalize%20on%20these%20advantages%20by%20explicitly%20painting%20the%20city%20as%20a%20safe%20spot%20to%20ride%20out%20the%20county's%20coming%20climate%20upheaval.%20In%20a%202019%20speech%2C%20Mayor%20Byron%20Brown%20said%20the%20city%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bclimate%20refuge%26quot%3B%20for%20Americans%20seeking%20a%20more%20stable%20place%20to%20lay%20down%20roots%20and%20promised%20to%20make%20investments%20in%20the%20city's%20resiliency.%20The%20declaration%20has%20been%20followed%20up%20with%20investments%20in%20key%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20climate%20resilience%20was%20one%20of%20the%20four%20pillars%20that%20made%20up%20the%20city's%20four-year%20strategic%20plan%20released%20at%20the%20start%20of%202023.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20plan%2C%20Buffalo's%20government%20said%20it%20planned%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20more%20resilient%20local%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackouts-power-outages-more-common-climate-change-electric-grid-infrastructure-2023-3%5C%22%3Eelectricity%20grid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20convert%20city%20vehicles%20and%20buildings%20to%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20invest%20in%20emissions-reducing%20infrastructure%20such%20as%20electric-vehicle%20charging%20stations%20and%20improved%20bike%20lanes.%20Beyond%20direct%20investment%2C%20the%20city%20also%20committed%20to%20working%20with%20private%20businesses%20to%20reduce%20their%20climate%20impact%2C%20including%20financing%20that%20allows%20companies%20to%20make%20energy-efficient%20upgrades%20to%20their%20facilities%20on%20the%20cheap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20many%20questions%20about%20the%20rollout%20of%20the%20plans%2C%20the%20vocal%20commitment%20of%20Buffalo%20to%20make%20the%20changes%20needed%20to%20make%20the%20city%20more%20climate-resilient%20will%20likely%20act%20as%20a%20clarion%20call%20for%20many%20Americans.%20Each%20year%2C%20roughly%208%20million%20Americans%20move%20to%20a%20different%20state.%20If%201%25%20of%20these%20movers%20chose%20Buffalo%2C%20this%20would%20be%20an%20inflow%20of%2080%2C000%20people%20to%20a%20city%20home%20to%20275%2C000%20people%20%E2%80%94%20a%20massive%20increase.%20And%20Buffalo%20isn't%20the%20only%20city%20in%20the%20country's%20industrial%20belt%20trying%20to%20win%20over%20new%20residents%20with%20this%20sales%20pitch%3A%20Places%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F03%2F10%2Frealestate%2Fduluth-minnesota-climate-change.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDuluth%2C%20Minnesota%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greatlakesnow.org%2F2023%2F06%2Fclimate-migrants-offset-michigans-population-woes-maybe-experts-say%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGrand%20Rapids%2C%20Michigan%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagobusiness.com%2Fforum-ideas-climate-migrants%2Fhow-chicagos-climate-could-become-its-big-advantage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChicago%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20making%20a%20bid%20for%20free-moving%20and%20climate-concerned%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProving%20they're%20the%20places%20to%20be%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20competition%20is%20still%20just%20one%20aspect%20of%20the%20battle%20between%20cities.%20Other%20factors%2C%20such%20as%20schools%2C%20crime%2C%20and%20job%20availability%2C%20are%20also%20crucial%20to%20developing%20the%20image%20as%20an%20up-and-coming%20place%20to%20move.%20Many%20of%20the%20cities%20that%20are%20trying%20to%20offer%20themselves%20to%20%26quot%3Bclimate%20refugees%26quot%3B%20have%20struggled%20with%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20elements%20in%20the%20recent%20past%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20is%20hope%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouseholds%20and%20individuals%20are%20able%20to%20make%20an%20informed%20decision%20about%20where%20to%20live%20based%20on%20a%20wealth%20of%20data%2C%20on%20things%20including%20home%20prices%2C%20graduation%20rates%20for%20public%20schools%2C%20and%20job%20openings.%20For%20concerns%20such%20as%20crime%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcde.ucr.cjis.gov%2FLATEST%2Fwebapp%2F%23%2Fpages%2Fexplorer%2Fcrime%2Fcrime-trend%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFBI%20has%20a%20tool%20on%20its%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20allow%20people%20to%20compare%20data%20for%20different%20cities%20and%20states%20across%20the%20country.%20As%20we%20start%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20emerging%20climate%20risks%20to%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20the%20US%20government%20can%20play%20a%20similar%20role%20in%20providing%20city-level%20data%20including%20recent%20temperature%20by%20month%2C%20air%20pollution%2C%20natural-disaster%20damage%2C%20and%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20most%20climate-resilient%20cities%20will%20become%20the%20clear%20winners.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real-estate%20firm%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fnews%2Fredfin-users-interact-with-flood-risk-data%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERedfin%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20partnered%20with%20the%20nonprofit%20First%20Street%20Foundation%20to%20provide%20property-level%20report%20cards%20on%20fire%2C%20flood%2C%20and%20heat%20risk%20to%20people%20searching%20for%20housing.%20My%20ongoing%20research%20highlights%20that%20homebuyers%20in%20both%20red%20states%20and%20blue%20states%20have%20begun%20to%20make%20decisions%20based%20on%20this%20information%2C%20weighing%20it%20as%20a%20factor%20in%20where%20they%20choose%20to%20move.%20As%20extreme%20weather%20events%20occur%2C%20people%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20home%20will%20be%20able%20to%20evaluate%20how%20many%20people%20died%20or%20lost%20their%20homes%20in%20any%20given%20city%20because%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20most%20climate-resilient%20cities%20will%20become%20the%20clear%20winners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20cities%20such%20as%20Buffalo%20and%20Detroit%20invested%20in%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%94%20from%20new%20roads%20and%20renewable-power%20plants%20to%20entertainment%20districts%20and%20improved%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20to%20support%20movers%2C%20this%20would%20act%20as%20a%20self-reinforcing%20economic%20cycle%20that%20could%20enhance%20their%20natural%20weather%20advantages.%20As%20the%20population%20grows%2C%20new%20restaurants%20and%20cultural%20opportunities%20will%20pop%20up.%20Home%20prices%20will%20grow%2C%20creating%20local%20wealth%20and%20economic%20development.%20And%20the%20spending%20on%20activities%20and%20housing%20will%20boost%20local%20tax%20revenues%20and%20provide%20cities%20a%20chance%20to%20reinvest%20in%20core%20services%20%E2%80%94%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bdoom%20loop.%26quot%3B%20But%20public-sector%20investment%20alone%20won't%20go%20very%20far%20without%20the%20innovation%20of%20the%20private%20sector.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorthern%20and%20Midwestern%20states%20will%20need%20a%20strong%20private-sector%20presence%20to%20meet%20the%20ever%20evolving%20demands%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20a%20wave%20of%20new%20residents%20will%20bring.%20Here%2C%20too%2C%20there%20are%20hopeful%20examples.%20In%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Pittsburgh%20suffered%20a%20sharp%20decline%20when%20its%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20goose%26quot%3B%20of%20steel%20production%20declined.%20In%20recent%20decades%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fview%2Farticles%2F2018-02-13%2Fpittsburgh-shows-the-way-to-a-rust-belt-rebound%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20city%20has%20made%20a%20dramatic%20comeback%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbrains%20economy%26quot%3B%20featuring%20robotics%20firms%20working%20with%20researchers%20at%20nearby%20universities%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20health-innovation%20economy.%20After%20decades%20of%20decline%2C%20census%20estimates%20show%20that%20the%20Pittsburgh%20area's%20population%20finally%20leveled%20off%20from%202010%20to%202022%20and%20suggest%20that%20the%20number%20of%20people%20living%20in%20the%20city%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pghcitypaper.com%2Fnews%2Fwhere-is-pittsburghs-population-growth-occurring-and-who-is-driving-it-20072229%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20bounce%20back%20in%20the%20coming%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Pittsburgh's%20rebound%20offers%20an%20optimistic%20case%20study%20for%20other%20Rust%20Belt%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20climate%20'Super%20Bowl'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20climate%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20sudden%20migration%20of%20Americans%20to%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20country.%20Many%20people%20still%20stick%20close%20to%20home%3A%20A%202015%20report%20from%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20found%20that%20the%20average%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2015%2F12%2F24%2Fupshot%2F24up-family.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20lived%20only%2018%20miles%20from%20their%20mother%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20the%20cities%20that%20could%20become%20climate%20havens%20have%20their%20weather%20downsides%20%E2%80%94%20Buffalo%20will%20still%20have%20some%20harsh%20winters%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20in%20small%20numbers%2C%20regional%20migration%20will%20have%20serious%20downstream%20effects%20on%20America's%20cities.%20If%20Buffalo%2C%20Detroit%2C%20Pittsburgh%2C%20and%20other%20cities%20succeed%20in%20their%20climate-resilience%20agendas%2C%20they%20will%20grow%2C%20attracting%20residents%20from%20more%20at-risk%20areas%20of%20the%20country.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20will%20force%20at-risk%20cities%20such%20as%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Miami%2C%20and%20Phoenix%20to%20invest%20more%20to%20offset%20their%20heat%20and%20flood%20risk.%20Even%20on%20a%20city%20level%2C%20competition%20fosters%20innovation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20great%20%26quot%3BSuper%20Bowl%26quot%3B%20of%20climate%20competition%20will%20spur%20our%20collective%20adaptation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMatthew%20E.%20Kahn%20is%20the%20Provost%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20and%20a%20Visiting%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Hoover%20Institution.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%202010%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-64160-20%26h%3D615e97aa1fb4cf09b4348f45ef391b5dc592d42d73dcf3ada6d3643224acfe85%26postID%3D6538eb20b5f87e160e0fed31%26postSlug%3Dcities-americans-move-cheap-homes-good-infrastructure-fewer-natural-disasters-2023-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FClimatopolis-Cities-Thrive-Hotter-Future%252Fdp%252F0465063837%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimatopolis%3A%20How%20Our%20Cities%20Will%20Thrive%20in%20the%20Hotter%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20the%202021%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-64160-20%26h%3D98798b828d4572d3bf006e8970babec4ff145cc9171218582122f6c1250f2a2c%26postID%3D6538eb20b5f87e160e0fed31%26postSlug%3Dcities-americans-move-cheap-homes-good-infrastructure-fewer-natural-disasters-2023-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FAdapting-Climate-Change-Management-Uncertain%252Fdp%252F0300246714%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdapting%20to%20Climate%20Change%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-americans-move-cheap-homes-good-infrastructure-fewer-natural-disasters-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698918421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65429a8a36d588dc55c8571f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-americans-move-cheap-homes-good-infrastructure-fewer-natural-disasters-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20newest%20sales%20pitch%20for%20American%20cities%3A%20Cheap%20homes%2C%20nice%20roads%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20catast