eptember%2C%20when%20it%20was%207.09%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20added%20that%20rural%20unemployment%20jumped%20from%206.2%25%20to%2010.82%25%20and%20that%20the%20urban%20employment%20rate%20%E2%80%9Ceased%20slightly%E2%80%9D%20to%208.44%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1966154%5C%22%3Egovernment%20figures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%202022-2023%20stood%20at%203.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20economists%20have%20come%20to%20rely%20on%20CMIE%20data%20for%20a%20better%20assessment%20of%20the%20labour%20market%20as%20its%20figures%20are%20based%20on%20monthly%20surveys%20as%20opposed%20to%20government%20data%2C%20which%20releases%20country-wide%20data%20less%20frequently%2C%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20economy%20was%20projected%20to%20rise%20by%20an%20impressive%206%25%20to%206.5%25%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20population%20is%20also%20growing%20and%20India%20overtook%20China%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20this%20growth%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-workforce-not-rising-quality-of-jobs-very-low-cmies-mahesh-vyas%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20workforce%20has%20remained%20stagnant%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20CMIE%20chief%20executive%20Mahesh%20Vyas%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClose%20to%2010%20million%20Indians%20entered%20the%20job%20market%20in%20October%20hoping%20to%20find%20work%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20cited%20CMIE%20data%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20found%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%2036%25%20of%20Indians%20aged%2015%20to%2034%20thought%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Ffor-15-34-yr-olds-top-concern-is-jobs-economic-struggles-survey-8897399%2F%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20was%20the%20biggest%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%20facing%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20compared%20to%20a%20similar%20survey%20conducted%20in%202016%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20Indians%20who%20identified%20unemployment%20as%20the%20biggest%20problem%20increased%20by%2018%20percentage%20points%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20the%20survey%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2040%25%20of%20educated%20respondents%20(graduate%20and%20above)%20identified%20unemployment%20as%20the%20biggest%20challenge%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20only%2027%25%20of%20non-literate%20individuals%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698914437000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25133033%2Fimage-1429.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Funemployment-rate-rose-to-10-09-percent-in-october-cmie-data%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unemployment%20is%20a%20persistent%20issue%20in%20India%20and%20experts%20say%20its%20workforce%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20despite%20the%20population%20and%20economy%20growing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Funemployment-rate-rose-to-10-09-percent-in-october-cmie-data%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Egypt%20says%20to%20help%20evacuate%20'about%207%2C000'%20Gaza%20foreign%20nationals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698914385000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104912040%2Cimgsize-140442.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fegypt-says-to-help-evacuate-about-7000-gaza-foreign-nationals%2Farticleshow%2F104911884.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5