sks%204%20States%20to%20Reconsider%20Criteria%20for%20Granting%20Minority%20Tag%20to%20Institutions%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22133252%2Fivan-aleksic-PDRFeeDniCk-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20National%20Commission%20for%20Minority%20Educational%20Institutions%20(NCMEI)%20has%20opposed%20the%20criteria%20fixed%20by%20four%20southern%20states%20for%20granting%20minority%20status%20to%20educational%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20criteria%2C%20an%20educational%20institution%20is%20granted%20minority%20status%20if%20they%20enrol%20between%2025-50%25%20of%20its%20students%20from%20a%20particular%20minority%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENCMEI%20has%20asked%20the%20four%20states%20to%20align%20with%20its%20criteria%20that%20require%20an%20institution%20seeking%20the%20minority%20tag%20to%20have%20admitted%20at%20least%20the%20same%20percentage%20of%20students%20from%20a%20particular%20minority%20community%20that%20matches%20its%20population%20share%20in%20the%20respective%20state%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fedugraph%2Fnational-commission-for-minority-educational-institutions-glare-on-high-ceiling-for-special-status%2Fcid%2F1976979%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%2C%20in%20place%20since%202018%2C%20an%20institution%20set%20up%20by%20a%20minority%20community%20needs%20to%20enrol%2050%25%20of%20its%20students%20from%20that%20community.%20This%20figure%20is%2030%25%20in%20Telangana%20and%2025%25%20in%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENCMEI%20member%20Shahid%20Akhter%2C%20in%20a%20meeting%20on%20October%2016%2C%20expressed%20displeasure%20at%20these%20criteria%20citing%20that%20such%20limits%20would%20deny%20minority%20status%20to%20institutions%20and%20discourage%20philanthropists%20from%20setting%20them%20up%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMinority%20communities%20are%20granted%20the%20power%20to%20set%20up%20and%20administer%20educational%20institutions%20to%20advance%20education%20in%20a%20particular%20community%20under%20the%20constitution.%20These%20institutions%20are%20exempted%20from%20implementing%20other%20reservation%20policies%20and%20are%20allowed%20to%20reserve%20up%20to%2050%25%20seats%20for%20students%20of%20a%20particular%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20has%20been%20observed%20that%20institutions%20set%20up%20by%20a%20particular%20community%20mostly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fedugraph%2Fnational-commission-for-minority-educational-institutions-glare-on-high-ceiling-for-special-status%2Fcid%2F1976979%5C%22%3Eenrol%20students%20from%20other%20communities%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3ETribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJose%20Abraham%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%20who%20has%20represented%20several%20petitioner%20institutions%20in%20the%20NCMEI%2C%20pointed%20out%20why%20that%20is%20the%20case.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20governments%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Karnataka%20are%20saying%20they%20would%20withdraw%20recognition%20to%20a%20school%20if%20it%20does%20not%20meet%20the%20required%20percentage%20of%20enrolment%20of%20children%20from%20the%20respective%20community.%20Imagine%20communities%20like%20Parsis%2C%20Jains%2C%20Christians%2C%20Buddhists%20and%20Sikhs%2C%20whose%20share%20in%20the%20population%20is%20very%20low.%20To%20ensure%2050%25%20enrolment%20from%20any%20one%20of%20these%20communities%20is%20impossible%2C%E2%80%9D%20Abraham%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fedugraph%2Fnational-commission-for-minority-educational-institutions-glare-on-high-ceiling-for-special-status%2Fcid%2F1976979%5C%22%3