04908128.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104908128.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%E2%80%8BShah%20Rukh%20Khan%3A%20Inspiring%20quotes%20by%20the%20actor%20about%20success%20and%20failure%E2%80%8B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fshah-rukh-khan-inspiring-quotes-by-the-actor-about-success-and-failure%2Fphotostory%2F104908128.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Electoral%20Bonds%3A%20Income%20from%20Unknown%20Sources%20to%20Political%20Parties%20Rose%20to%2072%25%20of%20Total%20Income%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20hearing%20the%20case%20on%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20against%20which%20multiple%20petitions%20have%20been%20filed.%20The%20arguments%20are%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArguing%20for%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20spoke%20on%20the%20need%20for%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20in%20order%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20unknown%20sources%20of%20income%20to%20political%20parties%20are%20minimised.%20His%20case%20on%20day%20two%20of%20the%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20included%20a%20read-out%20from%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20to%20speak%20of%20unknown%20donors%20from%20years%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepaper.thehindu.com%2Freader%3Futm_source%3DHindu%26utm_medium%3DMenu%26utm_campaign%3DHeader%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20calculating%20data%20on%20the%20source%20of%20political%20funding%2C%20has%20found%20that%20numbers%20are%20to%20the%20contrary.%20The%20source%20of%20funds%20from%20unknown%20sources%20to%20national%20parties%20in%20FY2015-FY2017%2C%20rose%20from%2066%25%20to%2072%25%20(nearly%20three-fourths)%20in%20FY2019-FY2022%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20were%20introduced%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20saw%20an%20increase%20from%2058%25%20being%20the%20share%20of%20unknown%20sources%20of%20income%20to%20total%20income%20to%2068%25%20in%20the%202019-2022%20period%2C%20that%20is%2C%20after%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20share%20(of%20unknown%20sources%20as%20a%20fraction%20of%20total%20income)%20remained%20around%2080%25%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20comprised%2081%25%20of%20the%20unknown%20funding%20to%20national%20parties%20in%20the%20period%20after%20they%20were%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Time%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftime-to-shut-the-floodgates-of-secret-political-party-funding%5C%22%3ETime%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKnown%20and%20unknown%20sources%20as%20per%20ADR%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnknown%20sources%20of%20income%2C%20as%20classified%20by%20election%20watchdog%20ADR%2C%20a%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case%2C%20is%20defined%20as%20income%20declared%20in%20the%20Annual%20Audit%20reports%20but%20without%20giving%20the%20source%20of%20income.%20This%20is%20for%20donations%20below%20Rs%2020%2C000.%20Such%20unknown%20sources%20include%20%E2%80%98Donations%20via%20Electoral%20Bonds%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98sale%20of%20coupons%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98relief%20fund%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98miscellaneous%20income%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98voluntary%20contributions%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98contribution%20from%20meetings%2F%20morchas%E2%80%99%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolitical%20parties%20are%20not%20required%20to%20reveal%20the%20name%20of%20individuals%20or%20organisations%20giving%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20known%20sources%20are%20defined%20as%20donations%20above%20Rs%2020%2C000.%20These%20are%20further%20classified%20by%20ADR%20into%20two%20types%20of%20incomes%2C%20one%2C%20whose%20donor%20details%20are%20submitted%20by%20parties%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20and%20another%20which%20comprise%20income%20through%20sales%20of%20movable%20and%20immovable%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPartywise%20share%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20according%20to%20ADR%20data%20used%20in%20this%20analysis%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20BJP%20secured%20Rs%205%2C%20721%20crore%20between%20FY2018%20and%20FY2022%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20This%20is%2057%25%20of%20all%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20issued%20till%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECongress%20got%20Rs%20952%20crore.%20That%20is%2010.4%25%20of%20the%20bonds.%C2%A0Trinamool%20Congress%20received%20Rs%20768%20crore%2C%C2%A0BJD%20Rs%20622%20crore%2C%20DMK%20432%20crore%2C%20BRS%20Rs%20384%20crore%20and%20YSRCP%20Rs%20330%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CPI(M)%20does%20not%20accept%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20is%20a%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case%20contesting%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20only%20political%20party%20so%20far%2C%20to%20go%20to%20court%20on%20this%2C%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20467px)%2085vw%2C%20467px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02114845%2FScreenshot-2023-11-02-at-11.48.18-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22467%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02114845%2FScreenshot-2023-11-02-at-11.48.18-AM.png%201133w%2C%