C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20Educational%2C%20Scientific%20and%20Cultural%20Organization%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funesdoc.unesco.org%2Fark%3A%2F48223%2Fpf0000384920%5C%22%3Ereleased%20a%20new%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailing%20how%20attacks%20against%20journalists%20are%20exacerbated%20during%20elections%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAttacks%20against%20journalists%20related%20to%20elections%20were%20registered%20by%20UNESCO%20in%20the%20context%20of%20at%20least%2089%20elections%20in%2070%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20from%20January%202019%20to%20June%202022.%20759%20journalists%20and%20media%20professionals%20were%20attacked%2C%2042%25%20(320)%20of%20whom%20were%20attacked%20by%20law%20enforcement%20agents%2C%20and%2029%25%20of%20attacked%20journalists%20(218)%20were%20women%2C%E2%80%9D%20UNESCO%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20UN%20body%20has%20highlighted%20the%20role%20of%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20(LEAs)%20in%20violence%20of%20this%20kind.%20%E2%80%9CLEAs%20have%20detained%20dozens%20of%20journalists%20covering%20protests%20in%20Asia%2C%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20North%20America%2C%20Europe%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20North%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Some%20of%20these%20arrests%20were%20temporary%20and%20either%20no%20charges%20were%20filed%2C%20or%20they%20were%20dropped%20later%20by%20authorities.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20journalists%20were%20arrested%20individually%3B%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20a%20number%20of%20journalists%20were%20arrested%20while%20covering%20protests%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%20situation%2C%20UNESCO%20has%20released%20the%20following%20guidelines%20for%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20across%20the%20world%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%202%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0Cultivate%20a%20good%20and%20professional%20relationship%20between%20LEAs%20and%20media%20outlets%20most%20likely%20to%20cover%20public%20demonstrations.%20Meet%20with%20journalists%20and%20talk%20about%20their%20different%20roles%20so%20there%20is%20more%20understanding%20within%20the%20community%20about%20what%20local%20LEAs%20are%20doing%20to%20keep%20them%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0Facilitate%20the%20work%20of%20journalists%2C%20providing%20as%20much%20access%20as%20is%20possible%20to%20a%20public%20assembly%20and%20to%20any%20related%20policing%20operation%20(e.g.%20identify%20press%20areas%2Fa%20defined%20media%20perimeter%20that%20will%20give%20them%20a%20safe%20vantage%20point%20and%20discuss%20these%20in%20advance%20with%20journalists).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0Protect%20the%20media%20and%20ensure%20a%20safe%20working%20environment%20by%20taking%20appropriate%20preventive%2C%20effective%20and%20timely%20operational%20measures%20%E2%80%93%20including%20police%20protection%20from%20attacks%20by%20the%20hostile%20groups.%20Particular%20attention%20should%20be%20devoted%20to%20the%20specific%20threats%20and%20risks%20that%20women%20journalists%20face%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20their%20work%2C%20and%20it%20is%20important%20to%20take%20a%20gender-sensitive%20approach%20when%20considering%20measures%20to%20address%20the%20safety%20of%20journalists%2C%20especially%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0LEAs%20should%20not%20use%20any%20form%20of%20obstruction%2C%20force%20or%20pressure%20against%20journalists%3B%20media%E2%80%99s%20professional%20equipment%20should%20be%20respected%20at%20all%20times%20(confiscation%20and%20damaging%20of%20their%20equipment%20is%20unlawful).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0No%20authorisation%20can%20be%20required%20of%20journalists%20wanting%20to%20report%20on%20events%20of%20public%20interest%2C%20however%2C%20special%20accreditation%20can%20be%20required%20for%20specific%20reasons%20of%20space%20or%20security%20(e.g.%20press%20conference%20with%20high-level%20officials%20and%20authorities).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0Encourage%20accredited%20members%20of%20the%20press%20to%20be%20easily%20identifiable%20by%20displaying%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CPRESS%E2%80%9D%20on%20their%20clothing%20and%20equipment%20in%20order%20to%20enable%20LEAs%20to%20better%20support%20them%20in%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%203%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0During%20elections%20it%20is%20vital%20for%20LEAs%20to%20liaise%20with%20Electoral%20Management%20Bodies%20(EMBs)%20throughout%20%E2%80%98The%20Election%20Cycle%E2%80%99%20and%20to%20remain%20neutral%20and%20demonstrate%20this%20neutrality%20through%20their%20communication%2C%20behaviour%20and%20the%20arrangements%20they%20put%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%97%8F%20%C2%A0Conduct%20regular%20training%20for%20LEAs%20during%20election%20periods%20and%20with%20journalists%20in%20covering%20public%20events.%20LEAs%20should%20attend%20regular%20refresher%20training%20sessions%20and%20briefings%20so%20they%20are%20up-to-date%20with%20any%20legislation%20affecting%20journalists%E2%80%99%20rights%20and%20any%20particular%20issues%20that%20might%20threaten%20their%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698902032000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07112943%2FScreenshot-2023-09-07-at-11.28.4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Funesco-releases-guidelines-for-law-enforcement-agencies-to-protect-journalists-during-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20important%2C%20the%20UN%20agency%20has%20said%2C%20because%20they%20have%20noticed%20an%20increase%20in%20attacks%20against%20journalists%20during%20elections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUr